openvpn (2.7~alpha3-debian0) stable; urgency=medium

  * OpenVPN Release 2.7_alpha3 (Gert Doering, 7b1b2834)
  * Fix wrong byte order of --dns server (Lev Stipakov, 63fed92c)
  * Fix DNS options duplication on PUSH_UPDATE (Lev Stipakov, 70d4c677)
  * Update systemd service name param to match command (Terrance, 8854550d)
  * Fix --dns options for TAP adapter (Lev Stipakov, 264fe916)
  * Fix broken DHCP options (Lev Stipakov, 040e0d1c)
  * dco-freebsd: pass address scope to the kernel (Kristof Provost, b5e0032b)
  * PUSH_UPDATE: Added update_option() function. (Marco Baffo, dd9c6978)
  * PUSH_UPDATE: Added remove_option() and do_update(). (Marco Baffo, 73f3247e)
  * PUSH_UPDATE: Allow OpenVPN in client mode to receive and handle PUSH UPDATE control messages to allow options updating at runtime. (Marco Baffo, 80b62545)
  * dco-freebsd: always enable float notification support (Kristof Provost, 796ad2c5)
  * options: Simplify function setenv_foreign_option (Frank Lichtenheld, 654671a1)
  * unit_tests/plugins/auth-pam: fix stdint.h related build error on fedora 42 (Gert Doering, 035d47e6)
  * mudp.c, multi.c, multi_io.c: get rid of 'all three DCO platforms' #ifdefs (Gert Doering, 6d0e3837)
  * dco: support float notifications on FreeBSD (Kristof Provost, b66b80b2)
  * dco_linux: clean up PEER_GET trigger and parser (Antonio Quartulli, d1f2afc2)
  * multi: make some multi_*() functions static (Antonio Quartulli, 3594f590)
  * add flag to print addresses in a consistent format during float (Ralf Lici, 7d5ec053)
  * dco_linux: fix async message reception (Antonio Quartulli, f353b710)
  * plugins: Clean up -Wconversion warnings (Frank Lichtenheld, df3ac551)
  * dco_linux: factor out netlink notification code (Antonio Quartulli, 0e0023fe)
  * dco: only pass struct context to init function (Antonio Quartulli, a699681b)
  * multi: store multi_context address inside top instance (Antonio Quartulli, 7f5a6dea)
  * dco_linux: rearrange functions (Antonio Quartulli, 7bcafb31)
  * dco_linux: use M_FATAL instead of M_ERR in netlink error code paths (Antonio Quartulli, dfe71b0a)
  * dco_linux: fix case statement by using proper error value (Antonio Quartulli, f1a2a378)
  * GHA: Dependency updates July 2025 (Frank Lichtenheld, 48f4a6a5)
  * improve float collision logging (Ralf Lici, 495e02e6)
  * Multi-socket: Fix assert triggered by stale peer-id reuse (Gianmarco De Gregori, fd93e4ad)
  * dco: Add support for float notifications (Ralf Lici, cb8a0f6f)
  * t_server_null: match test numbers with server numbers (Samuli Seppänen, 31aedd7f)
  * configure.ac: Remove use of PKCS11_HELPER_LIBS in mbedTLS checks (Frank Lichtenheld, ed690d1d)
  * README.dco: update Linux instructions (Antonio Quartulli, 3fdbad84)
  * reliable: Review and fix gc_arena usage (Frank Lichtenheld, 074bd745)
  * mac dns: do not run dns-updown in parallel (Heiko Hund, bc2c7429)
  * mac dns: compare servers before restoring backup (Heiko Hund, c1f44ea8)
  * Cleanup/simplify mbed TLS related define from autoconf (Arne Schwabe, 5f34a7a0)
  * move macOS dns-updown common code into functions (Heiko Hund, 022cd3e7)
  * prevent search domain races with macOS dns-updown (Heiko Hund, 4848df2f)
  * Fix compiler warning in reliable.c with --disable-debug (Frank Lichtenheld, fcd8f0f9)
  * dns: do not run updown scripts with lwipovpn (Heiko Hund, 4dc57d92)
  * Replace deprecated OpenSSL.crypto.load_crl (Christian Schürmann, f2364488)
  * t_server_null: add multi-socket testing (Samuli Seppänen, fd6d0f3c)
  * Added PQE to WolfSSL (rein.vanbaaren, 1b133cce)
  * Fix new doxygen warnings about using @return in void functions (Frank Lichtenheld, c18a995d)
  * packet_id: Fix build with --disable-debug (Frank Lichtenheld, 16c1da39)
  * dns: create NRPT registry key if it doesn't exist (Heiko Hund, df4863aa)
  * run forced --dns-updown without --script-security (Heiko Hund, cbf36218)
  * fix macOS dns-updown handling of parallel full redirects (Heiko Hund, 7a2b814f)
  * dco linux: avoid sending local port to ovpn (Ralf Lici, 6c2bd6be)
  * dco linux: avoid redefining ovpn enums (Ralf Lici, 1d3c2b67)
  * Route: add support for user defined routing table (Gianmarco De Gregori, f93fc813)
  * dns: add updown script for macOS (Heiko Hund, a4db3c6e)

